The 2nd China International Consumer Products Expo (Hainan Expo) kicked off today in Haikou, Hainan Province. Against the backdrop of a slowdown in the global economy, what role does the Hainan Expo play in boosting the economy? What kind of dividends will be sparked by the combination of Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership (RCEP) and the Hainan free-trade port? And ultimately, what is the significance of the expo? In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Aaron Liu has the answers.